ovember 2017  || {{fb|TAN}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20131 || rowspan=3 | Friendly\n|-\n| 22. || 11 June 2019  || [[Stade de Marrakech]], [[Marrakesh]], Morocco || {{fb|GUI}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130\n|-\n| 23. || 6 September 2019 || [[Stade Michel d'Ornano]], [[Caen]], France || {{fb|CIV}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20132\n|-\n| 24. || 13 November 2019 || [[Godswill Akpabio International Stadium]], [[Uyo]], Nigeria || {{fb|NGA}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20132 || [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group L|2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{LFP|id=sessegnon-stephane}}\n* {{ESPN FC|82488}}\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title=Benin squads\n| bg        = #FCD116\n| fg        = #008751\n| bordercolor = #E8112D\n|list1 =\n{{Benin squad 2008 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Benin squad 2010 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Benin squad 2019 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|list1=\n{{2008\u201309 Ligue 1 UNFP Team of the Year}}\n{{Sunderland A.F.C. Player of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sessegnon, Stephane}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Allah\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Beninese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Requins de l'Atlantique FC players]]\n[[Category:US Cr\u00e9teil-Lusitanos players]]\n[[Category:Le Mans FC players]]\n[[Category:Paris Saint-Germain F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sunderland A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Montpellier HSC players]]\n[[Category:Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:Benin Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Benin international footballers]]\n[[Category:2008 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:2010 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:2019 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:Beninese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Beninese expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n[[Category:Beninese expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Beninese expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|his cousin, the English footballer|Steven Sessegnon}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon\n| image       = St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon.jpg\n| image_size  = 250\n| caption     = Sess\u00e8gnon playing for West Bromwich Albion in 2013\n| fullname    = St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon<ref name=\"Premier League Clubs submit Squad Lists\">{{Cite news|title=Premier League Clubs submit Squad Lists |url=http://www.premierleague.com/content/dam/premierleague/site-content/News/publications/squad-lists/squad-lists-February-2013.pdf |publisher=Premier League |date=1 February 2013 |page=31 |access-date=24 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304033709/http://www.premierleague.com/content/dam/premierleague/site-content/News/publications/squad-lists/squad-lists-February-2013.pdf |archive-date=4 March 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1984|6|1|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Allah\u00e9]], Benin\n| height      = 1.68 m<ref>{{Cite web|title=Stephane Sessegnon Player Profile |url=http://www.espnfc.us/player/85095/stephane-sessegnon |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=7 May 2018}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]], [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|Attacking midfielder]], [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|Second striker]], [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]]\n| clubnumber  = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2000\u20132003\n| youthclubs1 = [[Requins de l'Atlantique FC|Requins de l'Atlantique]]\n| years1 = 2003\u20132004\n| clubs1 = [[Requins de l'Atlantique FC|Requins de l'Atlantique]]\n| caps1 =  \n| goals1 = \n| years2 = 2004\u20132006\n| clubs2 = [[US Cr\u00e9teil-Lusitanos|Cr\u00e9teil]]\n| caps2 = 68\n| goals2 = 10\n| years3 = 2006\u20132008\n| clubs3 = [[Le Mans Football Club|Le Mans]]\n| caps3 = 61\n| goals3 = 6\n| years4 = 2008\u20132011\n| clubs4 = [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n| caps4 = 77\n| goals4 = 9\n| years5 = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs5 = [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]\n| caps5 = 87\n| goals5 = 17\n| years6 = 2013\u20132016\n| clubs6 = [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]\n| caps6 = 79\n| goals6 = 8\n| years7 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs7 = [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]]\n| caps7 = 43\n| goals7 = 3\n| years8 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs8 = [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]]\n| caps8 = 63\n| goals8 = 8\n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Benin national football team|Benin]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 82\n| nationalgoals1 = 24\n| pcupdate = 19:45, 28 December 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = 23:00, 13 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon''' (born 1 June 1984) is a Beninese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Turkish club [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]]. He is a [[Benin national football team|Benin international]] having starred for the nation at both the [[2008 Africa Cup of Nations|2008]] and [[2010 Africa Cup of Nations|2010]] editions of the [[Africa Cup of Nations]]. Sess\u00e8gnon plays a variety of positions as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]], a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] and as a [[Midfielder|midfield]] offensive [[playmaker]]. He is Benin's [[List of top international men's association football goal scorers by country|all-time top scorer]] and appearance maker with 24 international goals in 82 matches.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nSess\u00e8gnon began his career in [[Cotonou]] with [[Benin Premier League]] side [[Requins de l'Atlantique FC|Requins de l'Atlantique]], which means the ''Sharks of the [[Atlantic Ocean|Atlantic]]'' in French. After spending only a year in the club's senior team, he moved to France to join [[US Cr\u00e9teil-Lusitanos|Cr\u00e9teil]], based in the [[Paris|Parisian suburbs]], where he joined fellow international [[No\u00ebl S\u00e9ka]]. Sess\u00e8gnon made his debut on the opening match day of the [[2004\u201305 Ligue 2]] season against [[Stade de Reims|Stade Reims]] as a substitute in a 2\u20131 defeat.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reims v. Creteil Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2004/2005&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J01&num_ordre=9 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120804041243/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2004/2005&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J01&num_ordre=9 |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 August 2012 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=6 August 2004 |access-date=29 June 2010 }}</ref> He scored his first goals on 14 January 2005, a brace in a span of four minutes, in a 3\u20130 win over [[FC Gueugnon|Gueugnon]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Creteil v. Gueugnon Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2004/2005&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J21&num_ordre=4 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120904230901/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2004/2005&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J21&num_ordre=4 |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 September 2012 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=14 January 2005 |access-date=29 June 2010 }}</ref> Though Cr\u00e9teil finished in 15th position, Sess\u00e8gnon was labeled a revelation as he was the primary bright spot in helping the club escape relegation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon, la r\u00e9v\u00e9lation de Cr\u00e9teil |url=http://www.20minutes.fr/article/48561/Sport-Sessegnon-la-revelation-de-Creteil.php |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120718233552/http://www.20minutes.fr/article/48561/Sport-Sessegnon-la-revelation-de-Creteil.php |url-status=dead |archive-date=18 July 2012 |work=20 Minutes |date=22 March 2005 |access-date=29 June 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Le Mans===\nKeen on a move to [[Ligue 1]], Sess\u00e8gnon signed a three-year deal with [[Le Mans Union Club 72|Le Mans]] on 19 May 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title=St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon signe 3 ans avec Le Mans |url=http://www.refletbenin.net/spip.php?article21 |work=Refleft Benin |date=19 May 2006 |accessdate=29 June 2010 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He made his debut for the club in a league match against [[Troyes AC|Troyes]], appearing as a substitute in a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le Mans v. Troyes Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006/2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J02&num_ordre=9 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=12 August 2006 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318060205/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006%2F2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J02&num_ordre=9 |archive-date=18 March 2007}}</ref> After featuring as a substitute in his first five appearances, and receiving a [[Ejection (sports)#Association football|straight red card]] in a match against [[CS Sedan Ardennes|Sedan]], he earned his first start on 4 November 2006 against [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sedan v. Le Mans Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006/2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J06&num_ordre=7 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=16 September 2006 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318060538/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006%2F2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J06&num_ordre=7 |archive-date=18 March 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Auxerre v. Le Mans Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006/2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J12&num_ordre=1 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=4 November 2006 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326030837/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006%2F2007&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=1&code_jr_tr=J12 |archive-date=26 March 2009}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored his first career goal for Le Mans in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rennes v. Le Mans Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006/2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J14&num_ordre=7 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=18 November 2006 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318101053/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2006%2F2007&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J14&num_ordre=7 |archive-date=18 March 2007}}</ref>\n\nInitially used as a [[Defensive midfielder|holding midfielder]] at Le Mans, Sess\u00e8gnon was given a more advanced role for the [[2007\u201308 Ligue 1|2007\u201308 season]], often starting on the [[Wide midfielder|right side of the midfield]] or as an [[Attacking midfielder|attacker]]. In this new role, he scored both goals in the club's 3\u20132 defeat to giants [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] on 1 September 2007.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le Mans v. Lyon Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007/2008&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J07&num_ordre=3 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=1 September 2007 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071208052017/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007%2F2008&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=3&code_jr_tr=J07 |archive-date=8 December 2007}}</ref> He scored again the following week in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Valenciennes FC|Valenciennes]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Le Mans v. Valenciennes Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007/2008&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J08&num_ordre=2 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120804014858/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007/2008&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J08&num_ordre=2 |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 August 2012 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=8 September 2007 |access-date=29 June 2010 }}</ref> Sess\u00e8gnon also helped the club reach the semi-finals of the [[Coupe de la Ligue]] that season although they lost to [[RC Lens|Lens]] in a thrilling 5\u20134 defeat in [[extra time]], Sess\u00e8gnon playing the entire 120 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le Mans v. Lens Match Report |url= http://www.lfp.fr/coupeLigue/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007/2008&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=T98&num_ordre=1 |archive-url= https://archive.is/20120903224642/http://www.lfp.fr/coupeLigue/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2007/2008&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=T98&num_ordre=1 |url-status= dead |archive-date= 3 September 2012 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=27 February 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Paris Saint-Germain===\n[[File:Sessegnon in 2009 match against Nice cropped.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Sess\u00e8gnon playing a match for [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|PSG]] against [[OGC Nice|Nice]].]]\nDue to his success at Le Mans, Sess\u00e8gnon was scouted by larger clubs such as [[Premier League]] sides [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080702161458/http://www.tribalfootball.com/article.php?id=96883 Arsenal, Newcastle maintain Sessegnon interest]. tribalfootball.com. 6 June 2008.</ref> and [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]. However, he remained in France by signing a four-year deal with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint Germain]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Benin ace claims Toon interest |url=http://sports.setanta.com/en/Sport/News/Football/2008/05/21/Prem-Ligue-1-Sessegnon-on-Newcastle-link/?facets/sport-space/football/ireland-locale/Newcastle/Barclays-Premier-League/ |work=Setanta Sports |date=21 May 2008 |accessdate=29 June 2010 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=PSG: Sessegnon arrive |url=http://www.mercato365.com/depeches/filinfo_250077_2514_PSG-Sessegnon-arrive.shtml |work=Mercato 365 |date=10 July 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090417160645/http://www.mercato365.com/depeches/filinfo_250077_2514_PSG-Sessegnon-arrive.shtml |archive-date=17 April 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=PSG sign Benin midfielder Sess\u00e8gnon |url= http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_kmafp/is_200807/ai_n27916734/|agency=Agence France-Presse |date=10 July 2008 |accessdate=29 June 2010 }} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref> The fee was said to be in the range of \u20ac8\u201310&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSG sign midfielder Sess\u00e8gnon |url= http://www.wsn.com/2008/07/11/football/news/france/psg-sign-benin-midfielder-sessegnon_336057/ |publisher=MSN |date=11 July 2008 |accessdate=29 June 2010}}</ref>\n\nSess\u00e8gnon made his league debut with the club on 16 August 2008, starting in the 1\u20130 win against [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]].<ref>{{cite news|title=PSG v. Bordeaux Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008/2009&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J02&num_ordre=8 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=16 August 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425062020/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008%2F2009&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=8&code_jr_tr=J02 |archive-date=25 April 2009 |df= }}</ref> The following match day, he scored his first goal for PSG in a 1\u20131 draw with [[FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard|Sochaux]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sochaux v. PSG Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008/2009&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J03&num_ordre=9 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=23 August 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091106232959/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008%2F2009&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=9&code_jr_tr=J03 |archive-date=6 November 2009}}</ref> On 13 December 2008, Sess\u00e8gnon scored his third career brace against Auxerre in a 2\u20131 victory.<ref>{{cite news |title=Auxerre v. PSG Match Report |url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008/2009&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J18&num_ordre=1 |work=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=13 December 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420084309/http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008%2F2009&code_evt=D1&num_ordre=1&code_jr_tr=J18 |archive-date=20 April 2009}}</ref> For his positive performances, he was named the [[UNFP Player of the Month]] for December.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon, la confirmation! |url= http://www.unfp.org/?id_rubrique=2824&id_trophee=82 |work=UNFP |date=29 December 2008 |accessdate=29 June 2010}}</ref> Sess\u00e8gnon also appeared in nine matches in the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], scoring one goal against Dutch club [[FC Twente|Twente]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Twente made to feel the PSG force |url=http://en.archive.uefa.com/competitions/uefacup/history/season=2009/round=15285/match=304240/index.html |publisher=UEFA |date=18 December 2008 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116082625/http://en.archive.uefa.com/competitions/uefacup/history/season%3D2009/round%3D15285/match%3D304240/index.html |archive-date=16 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nSeveral clubs contacted PSG in the off-season to discuss Sess\u00e8gnon's availability, with [[Premier League]] clubs [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]<ref>[http://www.footylatest.com/man-city-chelsea-and-everton-alerted-by-breakdown-in-sessegnon-contract-talks/6450 Man City, Chelsea and Everton alerted by breakdown in Sess\u00e8gnon contract talks] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090627014439/http://www.footylatest.com/man-city-chelsea-and-everton-alerted-by-breakdown-in-sessegnon-contract-talks/6450 |date=27 June 2009 }}. Footylatest.com. 23 June 2009. Retrieved 6 July 2012.</ref> being the primary suitors.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sessegnon open to Chelsea offer |url= https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=1051275.html |publisher=FIFA |date=24 April 2009 |accessdate=29 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Liverpool To Battle Chelsea for Talented \u00a312m Playmaker |url=http://www.caughtoffside.com/2009/05/31/liverpool-to-battle-chelsea-for-12m-playmaker/ |publisher=FIFA |date=31 May 2009 |access-date=29 June 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628184535/http://www.caughtoffside.com/2009/05/31/liverpool-to-battle-chelsea-for-12m-playmaker/ |archive-date=28 June 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Arsenal Set To Beat Chelsea For Sess\u00e8gnon |url=http://africanfootball.mtnfootball.com/live/content.php?Item_ID=19008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811053257/http://africanfootball.mtnfootball.com/live/content.php?Item_ID=19008 |url-status=dead |archive-date=11 August 2011 |work=MTN Football |date=14 April 2009 |access-date=29 June 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Man City, Chelsea and Everton alerted by breakdown in Sess\u00e8gnon contract talks |url=http://www.footylatest.com/man-city-chelsea-and-everton-alerted-by-breakdown-in-sessegnon-contract-talks/6450 |work=Footy Latest |date=23 June 2009 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090627014439/http://www.footylatest.com/man-city-chelsea-and-everton-alerted-by-breakdown-in-sessegnon-contract-talks/6450 |archive-date=27 June 2009}}</ref> Taking advantage of the considerable interest in him, Sess\u00e8gnon issued a public demand on 23 June that his parent club give him a pay raise, stating, \"I think I am one of the best performers in the club.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon wants new deal |url= http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11671_5397332,00.html |work=Sky Sports |date=23 June 2009 |accessdate=29 June 2010}}</ref> The firing of PSG manager [[Paul Le Guen]] also played a role in his demands, and two weeks later, Sess\u00e8gnon and the club reached an agreement on a contract extension with the player set to receive a substantial pay raise.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon signs PSG extension |url= http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11095_5420103,00.html |work=Sky Sports |date=7 July 2009 |accessdate=29 June 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2010\u201311 in French football|2010\u201311 season]], Sess\u00e8gnon struggled to make an impact with the first team after manager [[Antoine Kombouar\u00e9]] relegated him to a substitute's role. Friction between player and manager reached its zenith in December 2010, when Sess\u00e8gnon accused Kombouar\u00e9 of insulting him during a one-on-one interview ahead of the team's match against [[AS Nancy|Nancy]] on 19 December.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon: \"Kombouar\u00e9 m'a insult\u00e9\" |url=http://fr.sports.yahoo.com/23122010/70/ligue-1-sessegnon-kombouare-m-a-insulte.html |work=Yahoo Sports! |date=23 December 2010 |access-date=27 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101227061838/http://fr.sports.yahoo.com/23122010/70/ligue-1-sessegnon-kombouare-m-a-insulte.html |archive-date=27 December 2010}}</ref> Sess\u00e8gnon subsequently confirmed his desire to leave the club in the January window and, as a sign of his intent, refused to join Paris Saint-Germain on its winter training camp in Morocco.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sess\u00e8gnon left at home whilst Deschamps wants security |url=http://www.adifferentleague.co.uk/p6_1_5728_ligue-1-daily-sessegnon-left-at-home-whilst-deschamps-wants-security.html |work=A Different League |date=8 January 2011 |access-date=27 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110112030714/http://www.adifferentleague.co.uk/p6_1_5728_ligue-1-daily-sessegnon-left-at-home-whilst-deschamps-wants-security.html |archive-date=12 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Sunderland===\n\n====2010\u201311 season====\n[[File:St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon Sunderland.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Sess\u00e8gnon playing for Sunderland in 2011.]]\nOn 29 January 2011, Sess\u00e8gnon departed Paris Saint-Germain to join English club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]].<ref>{{cite news |title=St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon \u00e0 Sunderland |url= http://www.psg.fr/fr/Article/003001/Article/52252/Stephane-Sessegnon-a-Sunderland |work=A Different League |date=29 January 2011 |accessdate=29 January 2011 | language = German}}</ref> He signed a three-and-a-half-year contract and the transfer fee was priced at \u00a36&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite news |title=Sunderland sign St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon for \u00a36m and Sulley Muntari on loan |url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2011/jan/30/stephane-sessegnon-sunderland-sulley-muntari |work=[[Guardian Media Group]] |date=29 January 2011 |accessdate=29 January 2011 |location=London}}</ref> and made his debut on 1 February against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9379797.stm|title=Sunderland 2\u20134 Chelsea|author=Saj Chowdhury|date=1 February 2011|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=2 February 2011}}</ref> He made his second start for the ''Black Cats'' in 3\u20132 away loss against [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on 5 February 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9386882.stm|title=Stoke 3 \u2013 2 Sunderland|author=Mark Ashenden |date=5 February 2011|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=5 February 2011}}</ref> His first real successful moment as a Sunderland player after a disappointing start came on 23 April, where he scored his first goal for the club in the 4\u20132 win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]. He converted a penalty of his own making in the 73rd minute, beating [[Ali Al-Habsi]] after being tripped by [[Antol\u00edn Alcaraz]]. Sess\u00e8gnon had been forced to play in an unfamiliar role as a lone striker, after injuries to strikers [[Danny Welbeck]] and [[Asamoah Gyan]] during the match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9463428.stm|title=Sunderland 4\u20132 Wigan Athletic|author=Angus Lovely|date=22 April 2011|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref>\n\nSess\u00e8gnon scored in Sunderland's home defeat against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]],<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9483162.stm | publisher=BBC News | title=Sunderland 1\u20133 Wolves | date=14 May 2011}}</ref> and again in the final match of the season, a 0\u20133 win at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/2896/premier-league/2011/05/22/2498316/west-ham-united-0-3-sunderland-zenden-sessegnon-riveros|title= West Ham United 0\u20133 Sunderland: Zenden, Sessegnon & Riveros goals send Hammers down with a whimper|website= Goal.com|date= 22 May 2011|accessdate= 6 July 2012}}</ref>\n\n====2011\u201312 season====\n[[File:Stephane Sessegnon cropped.jpg|thumb|left|upright|150px|Sess\u00e8gnon playing for Sunderland in 2012]]\nIn his second season at Sunderland, Sess\u00e8gnon scored his first goal of the season against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] on 22 October 2011. He followed this up with an 89th-minute equaliser against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] a week later, also providing an assist and winning man of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ukpress/article/ALeqM5jbqAw7PibIzBN-5rQ1j3Fo2Sy_hA?docId=N0346811319899010348A |accessdate=30 October 2011 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 February 2012, in a FA Cup fourth round replay, Sess\u00e8gnon scored a dramatic late winner against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] in the 113th minute during extra time to take Sunderland into the fifth round again Arsenal.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16828795 BBC Sport \u2013 Middlesbrough 1\u20132 Sunderland]. BBC. 7 February 2012. Retrieved 6 July 2012.</ref> On 4 March, he was sent-off in the match against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] for an elbow to the chest of [[Cheick Tiot\u00e9]], with Sunderland leading the [[Tyne-Wear derby]] 1\u20130. Newcastle went on to equalise in stoppage time. Sess\u00e8gnon served a three-match ban<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunderland's Lee Cattermole and St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon to miss Everton tie|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/mar/06/sunderland-cattermole-sessegnon-everton-fa-cup|work=The Guardian|date=6 March 2012|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> returning to score the third goal in Sunderland's 3\u20131 win against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] at the [[Stadium of Light]] on 24 March. Against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], although he did not score in the match, he set up two assists, one for a [[Sebastian Larsson]] opener in the 31st minute and the second for a [[Nicklas Bendtner]] header deep in the first half of injury time to make the match 2\u20131 for Sunderland at half time. The match finished in a 3\u20133 draw, with Larsson in the 55th minute scoring to put Sunderland 3\u20131 ahead after Sess\u00e8gnon started that attack, then in the 85th minute, [[Mario Balotelli]] scored to make the score 3\u20132 and [[Aleksandar Kolarov]] scored Manchester City's equalising goal in the 86th.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-sland/238181|title=City sidestep Sunderland upset|date=31 March 2012|accessdate = 1 September 2017}}</ref> Sess\u00e8gnon won the Player of the Season award for the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pair take top awards|url=http://www.safc.com/news/20120510/pair-take-top-awards_2256213_2765071|publisher=Sunderland A.F.C.|date=10 May 2012|accessdate=10 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n====2012\u201313 season====\nOn 30 August 2012, Sess\u00e8gnon signed a new contract that would keep him at the Stadium of Light until 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sessegnon signs new deal|url=http://www.safc.com/news/team-news/2012/august/sessegnon-signs-new-deal|publisher=SAFC Sport|accessdate=30 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Paolo Di Canio]]'s second match as Sunderland manager, on 14 April 2013, Sess\u00e8gnon scored against Sunderland's fiercest rivals Newcastle to put Sunderland 1\u20130 up. Sunderland went on to win the encounter with their rivals 3\u20130, with Sess\u00e8gnon assisting [[David Vaughan (footballer)|David Vaughan]] for the third goal. The following week, Sess\u00e8gnon scored the only goal as Sunderland defeated [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] 1\u20130 at home. His season ended prematurely after he was sent off during Sunderland's 6\u20131 defeat against Aston Villa.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aston Villa F.C vs Sunderland A.F.C.|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22244165|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=29 April 2013|date=29 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n===West Bromwich Albion===\nOn 2 September 2013, Sess\u00e8gnon joined [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] for a club record fee of \u00a35.5&nbsp;million, rising to \u00a36&nbsp;million with extras.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/west-bromwich-albion-fc/2013/09/02/west-brom-break-record-for-stephane-sessegnon/| title=West Brom break record for Stephane Sessegnon|access-date = 2 September 2013}}</ref> On 21 September, Sess\u00e8gnon scored the first goal in a 3\u20130 win on his debut for [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] against Sunderland, his previous club.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24089796|title=West Brom 3\u20130 Sunderland|first=Becky|last=Ashton|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=21 September 2013|accessdate=24 September 2013}}</ref> On 9 November, he scored against Chelsea in controversial 2\u20132 draw at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24783075|title=Chelsea 2\u20132 West Bromwich Albion|first=Sam|last=Sheringham|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=9 November 2013|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref> On 15 March 2014, Sessegnon scored the first Albion goal of a 1\u20132 away victory against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] at the [[Liberty Stadium]], helping [[Pepe Mel]] gain his first win as head coach.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26493268|title=Swansea City 1\u20132 West Bromwich Albion|first=Rob|last=Westall|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=15 March 2014|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref> Sess\u00e8gnon, thus far, has been a fan favourite at the club and his substitution in matches has often lead to a negative reaction from the fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/west-bromwich-albion-fc/2014/11/29/alan-irvine-responds-to-criticism-at-west-brom/|title=Alan Irvine responds to criticism at West Brom|website=Express & Star}}</ref> He scored his first goal of his second season at the club against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] with a well-taken strike in a 2\u20132 draw at [[The Hawthorns]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/premier-league/11174511/West-Bromwich-Albion-2-Manchester-United-2-Daley-Blind-and-Marouane-Fellaini-rescue-point-for-Louis-van-Gaals-side.html|title=West Bromwich Albion 2 Manchester United 2: Daley Blind and Marouane Fellaini save point for Louis van Gaal|first=Henry|last=Winter|date=20 October 2014|via=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref>\n\nAfter almost leaving the club at the end of the season after falling out with manager [[Tony Pulis]] over selection issues, Sessegnon would return to the first team in the [[2015-16 Premier League|2015\u201316 season]] with consistent performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/west-bromwich-albion-fc/2015/05/18/stephane-sessegnon-closer-to-albion-exit/|title=Stephane Sessegnon closer to Albion exit|website=Express & Star}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tony-pulis-stphane-sessgnon-set-10619838|title=Tony Pulis: St\u00e9phane Sess\u00e8gnon set for West Brom return against Bournemouth|first=Mat|last=Kendrick|date=18 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3383171/Saido-Berahino-follow-Stephane-Sessegnon-s-example-urges-West-Brom-midfielder-Darren-Fletcher.html|title=Fletcher: Saido Berahino must follow Stephane Sessegnon's example|date=4 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 May 2016, it was announced that Sess\u00e8gnon and [[Victor Anichebe]] would leave the club.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Albion confirm Hawthorns departures |url=http://www.wba.co.uk/news/article/west-brom-albion-contracts-sessegnon-anichebe-morrison-3117887.aspx |publisher=West Bromwich Albion F.C. |date=18 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Montpellier===\nOn 26 September 2016, Sess\u00e8gnon signed for [[Ligue 1]] side [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] on a two-year deal.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Sessegnon \u00e0 Montpellier (off.) |url=http://sport24.lefigaro.fr/football/ligue-1/Homes-Clubs/montpellier/fil-info/sessegnon-a-montpellier-off.-826337 |publisher=sport24.fr |date= 26 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi===\nOn 23 January 2018, Sess\u00e8gnon signed a one and a half-year contract with [[S\u00fcper Lig]] side [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=YEN\u0130 TRANSFER\u0130M\u0130Z STEPHANE SESSEGNON |url=http://genclerbirligi.org.tr/yeni-transferimiz-stephane-sessegnon/|publisher=Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. |date= 28 January 2018|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nSess\u00e8gnon made his debut for [[Benin national football team|Benin]] on 6 June 2004 in a [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2006 World Cup qualification match]] against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] starting in the team's 2\u20131 loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cameroon&nbsp;\u2013 Benin Match Report |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/germany2006/preliminaries/preliminary=7381/matches/match=35845/report.html |publisher=FIFA |date=6 June 2004 |access-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091013142418/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/germany2006/preliminaries/preliminary%3D7381/matches/match%3D35845/report.html |archive-date=13 October 2009 |df= }}</ref>\n[[File:StephaneSessegnon.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Sess\u00e8gnon signing autographs in 2009]]\n\n==Style of play==\nUpon signing for [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], manager [[Steve Bruce]] described Sess\u00e8gnon as a player who \"can play on the left, on the right, through the middle \u2013 he's lightning quick and he's a match-winner.\" Bruce also went on to say, \"St\u00e9phane's a little powerhouse with a low centre of gravity, some great dribbling skills and a good shot.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110202211653/http://www.safc.com/news/20110129/bruce-on-sessegnon-capture-_2256213_2279712|title=Bruce on Sess\u00e8gnon capture|date=29 January 2011|publisher=Sunderland A.F.C.|accessdate=2 February 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is a distant cousin of twin brothers [[Ryan Sessegnon|Ryan]], who plays for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C|Tottenham Hotspur]]\nand [[Steven Sessegnon|Steven]], who plays for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].\n==Honors==\n===Club===\n'''PSG'''\n*[[Coupe de France]]:[[2009-10 Coupe de France|2009-10]]<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20100706165912/http://www.fff.fr/compint/65318/match/65430.shtml</ref>\n===National===\n'''Benin'''\n* Four Nations Tournament (Ghana) silver:2007<ref>http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/gha-4nat-07.html</ref>\n===Individual===\n*Special Award for services to the national team<ref>https://www.goal.com/en-kw/news/sessegnon-buoyed-up-by-benin-football-award-ahead-of-afcon/158wd0xzvvcqs149vvyftrpip5</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 28 December 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway|1239}}</ref><ref name=\"nft\">{{cite web|title=Stephane Sessegnon|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/7756/Stephane_Sessegnon.html|website=Soccerbase|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|title=Sess\u00e8gnon, St\u00e9phane|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/7756/Stephane_Sessegnon.html|website=National-Football-Teams|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[US Cr\u00e9teil-Lusitanos|Cr\u00e9teil]]\n|[[2004\u201305 Ligue 2|2004\u201305]]\n|[[Ligue 2]]\n|35||5||0||0||0||0||0||0||35||5\n|-\n|[[2005\u201306 Ligue 2|2005\u201306]]\n|Ligue 2\n|33||5||0||0||0||0||0||0||33||5\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!68||10||0||0||0||0||0||0||68||10\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Le Mans Football Club|Le Mans]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Ligue 1|2006\u201307]]\n|[[Ligue 1]]\n|31||1||0||0||0||0||0||0||31||1\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Ligue 1|2007\u201308]]\n|Ligue 1\n|30||5||0||0||0||0||0||0||30||5\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!61||6||0||0||0||0||0||0||61||6\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n|Ligue 1\n|34||6||2||1||4||0||9{{efn|