 Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Second Round|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 17. || rowspan=2 | 27 March 2016  || rowspan=2 | {{fb|SSD}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\"| 4\u20131 || rowspan=3 | 2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification\n|-\n| 18. || align=center | '''4'''\u20131\n|-\n| 19. || 4 September 2016 || Stade du 26 Mars, Bamako, Mali || {{fb|MLI}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20135 || align=center | 2\u20135 \n|-\n| 20. || 11 June 2017 || rowspan=2 | Stade de l'Amiti\u00e9, Cotonou, Benin || {{fb|GAM}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130 || [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group D|2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|-\n| 21. || 12 November 2017  || {{fb|TAN}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20131 || rowspan=3 | Friendly\n|-\n| 22. || 11 June 2019  || [[Stade de Marrakech]], [[Marrakesh]], Morocco || {{fb|GUI}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130\n|-\n| 23. || 6 September 2019 || [[Stade Michel d'Ornano]], [[Caen]], France || {{fb|CIV}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20132\n|-\n| 24. || 13 November 2019 || [[Godswill Akpabio International Stadium]], [[Uyo]], Nigeria || {{fb|NGA}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20132 || [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group L|2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{LFP|id=sessegnon-stephane}}\n* {{ESPN FC|82488}}\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title=Benin squads\n| bg        = #FCD116\n| fg        = #008751\n| bordercolor = #E8112D\n|list1 =\n{{Benin squad 2008 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Benin squad 2010 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Benin squad 2019 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|list1=\n{{2008\u201309 Ligue 1 UNFP Team of the Year}}\n{{Sunderland A.F.C. Player o